1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a method to learn a low-dimensional feature representation of the environment using an encoder-decoder neural network, which is a common technique in computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses deep neural networks to learn the feature representation and the decision policy, which falls under the category of machine learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper deals with autonomous driving, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics): Autonomous driving involves the use of robots (i.e., self-driving cars), which falls under the category of robotics. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the control of autonomous vehicles, which falls under the category of systems and control.
